OL,3,CInspection of maternity service finds
OL,4,C'babies could be put at risk of harm'
OL,6,FCarolyn Jenkinson, CQC's deputy
OL,7,Fdirector of secondary and specialist
OL,8,Fcare said, "When we inspected
OL,9,Fmaternity services at Horton General
OL,10,FHospital we found a service with poor
OL,11,Fgovernance and ineffective systems and
OL,12,Fprocesses which meant women, people
OL,13,Fusing the service and their babies
OL,14,Fcould be put at risk of harm.
OL,16,FIt's the first time maternity services
OL,17,Fat Horton General Hospital have been
OL,18,Frated as a standalone core service.
OL,19,FPreviously, maternity and gynaecology
OL,20,Fservices were inspected and rated
OL,21,Ftogether.
